@NODE AM "Setting DirOpus FileType"

  · Run your copy of DirOpus (5.11+)

  · Select the menu-item 'Settings/FileTypes...'

  · Click on the 'Add' button

  · Replace 'Untitled' by 'Font' (with no quotes)

  · Set ID to 'FONT' (also with no quotes)

  · 'Pri' remains '0'

  · Click on the 'Add' button

  · The word 'Match' appears both in the Listview gadget and above the 'Add'
    button

  · Now click on the folder gadget (just above the 'Add' gadget)

  · In the newly opened window, find 'Move To' and double-click on it

  · You'll notice that both 'Match'es are replaced by 'Move To'

  · Add '32' in the string gadget (with no quotes), and press RETURN

  · Hit the 'Add' button again

  · Replace the new 'Move To' by Match by using the 'folder gadget' again

  · Finally enter 'p?Nu' in the string gadget (with no quotes) and press
    'Use'


  · You'll now see a window titled 'Font'

  · Click on 'Double-click'

  · A new window is opened

  · Click on 'Add'

  · Set the 'Command'-gadget to 'AmigaDOS'  »» NOT TO WORKBENCH !!! ««

  · Use the folder gadget to select your copy of Shelley (If you have e.g.
    stored Shelley in SYS:Utilities  the string gadget should then display
    SYS:Utilities/Shelley after you have finished.)

  · Click on the argument gadget '{ }' at the right of the string gadget

  · double-click on '{f}' and press RETURN

  · No flags need to be set

  · Press the 'Use' button (You'll notice a tick besides 'Double-click'.)

  · Press the 'Use' button again and your new filetype has been defined

  · All you have to do is save it now


  · If  all went  right, double-clicking on  a font in DirOpus will cause a
    call to Shelley now, which will show you the font

@ENDNODE

